description: dapol oo gauge stanier non corridor coach in br carmine red livery  unlined  plastic model kit  manufacturers description  william stanier   was headhunted from the gwr to become chief mechanical engineer of london  midland and scottish  lms  railways in  with the support of the chairman  sir josiah stamp  stanier is credited with modernising the lms fleet of generally small steam locomotives with larger  modern and more powerful array of designs  soon after his appointment  stanier also focused on refurbishing and standardising the coach stock of the lms and developed the period iii lms coaches which later became known as stanier coaches  these designs were extremely popular and successful and many were still in service in the mid  s  there are many examples of period iii coaches operating on heritage railways throughout the uk today  the dapol oo model of the stanier coach is derived from refurbished airfix mainline tooling originally purchased by dapol in the  s  there are some compromises on detail accuracy due to the condition and usability of the  year old tooling  however  we feel the model captures the essence of the period iii coach design well and offers an extremely affordable way of building up fleet of pre or post nationalised fleet of lms coaches  dapol have strived to ensure livery and colour details have been captured and are comparable to the originals  including the roof level gold lines  the kit comes complete with decorated body  all that is required is painting of the roof and other components and assembly  please note that this item is not toy and is intended for model railway enthusiasts

product description object of the game to move one of your dice onto your opponent’s back line without that die being immediately taken by your opponent on their very next turn  set up each player takes either the red or black set of sixteen dice and prepares to set up at opposite ends of the board  players then simultaneously roll each of their sixteen dice  one at time  once rolled  each die is placed immediately on the board  this commences of the left square on player’s back row and continues across to the right  on completion of the back row  the dice are placed from the left again on the next row up  after each roll  each die must be placed onto the next available square  players cannot select on which square they would like to place each die  once both players have completed the set up  play commences  rules the player with the most sixes starts  if the players have the same amount  then the player with the most fives starts and so on players take one turn each alternately  player can move any one die the number of squares that corresponds to the number showing on that die  for example  if that number is  the player can move that die forwards  backwards  sideways or diagonally up or down in straight line over three squares  within the movement the die cannot pass over any other die  either an opponent’s die or their own if any move results in die landing on square occupied by an opponent’s die then the opponent’s die is ‘taken’ and removed from the board  instead of moving die on any turn player can opt to rotate one of their dice degrees  for example die with   showing can be turned over to   or whilst remaining on its current square  this movement constitutes player’s turn  winning the game the first player to get one of their dice onto any square along their opponent’s back row  which their opponent cannot then take on their very next turn  wins the game  box contains playing dice

how to apply  make sure you wash and thoroughly dry the application area of skin before applying the tattoo  any oils or creams on the skin will affect its adhesion  it is best to clean the application area with an alcohol wipe prior to application   transfer temporary tattoos are activated by water   remove any clear protective films that may be present protecting the tattoo   cut around the tattoo as close as possible to the design   place the tattoo face down on the area of skin where the tattoo is desired  ensure it is the correct way up   apply even pressure to the tattoo paper backing using wet cloth or sponge  wait about minimum of seconds and then remove the cloth and gently slide off the paper   allow the tattoo to dry naturally  how to remove  the transfer tattoos will come off naturally over few days just with normal washing   tattoos can be removed quickly and easily with either baby oil or an alcohol cleanser

description: metal helicopter  built in gyro the gyro is an essential component in many rc helicopters  gyros in rc helicopters are most commonly used to control unwanted movement on the yaw axis  when an rc helicopter rotates on its yaw axis  the direction the nose points  the heading  changes  the yaw gyro job is to sense any undesired rotation around the yaw axis  clockwise or counter clockwise rotation when viewed from above and to automatically correct the orientation of the rc helicopter  without yaw gyro  even if the rc helicopter was trimmed out to fly straight initially  it would eventually begin to drift and rotate right or left  normal maneuvering of the rc helicopter and external forces can result in undesired yaw rotation  when this occurs  the gyroscope senses this change in yaw and corrects it  this results in stable flight for the rc helicopter and no undesired changes in yaw  specification colour may vary  size  plane weight  main rotor diameter  tail rotor diameter  range  about or below flight duration  approx   charging time  about   hours battery    li poly transmitter battery  aa not included  function  forward backward up down left or right rotation item included helicopter   remote controller   charger   balance charger box   spare main blade   pair spare tail rotor blade   colour may vary

description: package sunnytech® package  great gift for boy or girl friend  parents  kids etc features  speed up to   rpm start temperaure difference oc color silver bottom gold flywheel material  steel and glass size weight warning  only use pencil powder to lubricate this stirling engine if need  prohibit to add oil to lubricate because the oil will mix with dust in the air  and become oil dirt  finally make the friction to be even bigger the stirling engine can run freely  what is the stirling engine? stirling engine is heat engine that operates by cyclic compression and expansion of air or other gas  the working fluid  at different temperature levels such that there is net conversion of heat energy to mechanical work the engine is like steam engine in that all of the engine heat flows in and out through the engine wall  how it works? this is traditionally known as an external combustion engine in contrast to an internal combustion engine where the heat input is by combustion of fuel within the body of the working fluid  unlike the steam engine use of water in both its liquid and gaseous phases as the working fluid the stirling engine encloses fixed quantity of permanently gaseous fluid such as air or helium  as in all heat engines  the general cycle consists of compressing cool gas  heating the gas  expanding the hot gas  and finally cooling the gas before repeating the cycle  you can put the stirling motor toy in top of hot water to make the temperature difference  you also can put it in top of ice to get the termperature difference  just enjoy the toy

no one really knows where john came from  he just showed up one day in the everglades on his houseboat  the gators didnt seem to pay him much attention  once in awhile  one would crawl up on his boat  and john would come out and talk to it in hushed tones until it wandered off folks found john strange  but it was clear he wasn trouble  just kindly old coot who kept to himself  all sorts of stories were made up about the strange  swamp dweller  but none came close to the truth  john rhodes was  in fact  the worlds most talented alchemist  and wielder of the philosophers stone john had always had an affinity for altering the very threads of existence  he could feel them as they stretched around him  connecting everything to everything else  so  when those lines drew him to mysterious  glowing stone  he knew it was right and proper to take it with him  the stone allows him to twist the lines  rather than just perceive them  and he can now easily transmute objects into other materials john  the scholar  mostly keeps to himself  though hes always willing to share bit of wisdom and bite to eat with anyone who passes by  however  now and again  he feels the ley lines pull and twang sharply  which shouldnt happen  hell travel from one place to another  easing the tension on the lines by stopping the odd  extra planar entity from entering this dimension  or keeping the crazed scientist from pulling the moon into the earth  or halting the nightmarish legions of comatose little girl  sometimes  hell work with other gentle souls to accomplish his goal he doesnt mind little company now and then  mainly he just wants to keep things copacetic

product description relatives visiting? hosting party? stuck in an airport? then it time for uno  the classic card game  which is quick to learn  easy to play and fun for all the family  the aim of the game is to be the first player to score points  by getting rid of all the cards in your hand before your opponents  you score points for all the cards left in your opponents  hands  the rules of uno are simple  every player picks card and the person who draws the highest number deals  action cards count as zero at this stage once the pack has been shuffled  each player is dealt cards  the remainder of the deck is placed face down to form draw pile  and the top card of the draw pile is turned over to start discard pile  the person to the left of the dealer starts play and has to match the card on the discard pile  either by number or colour  so  if the card is red  the player must put down red card or any card regardless of its colour  alternatively  the player can put down wild card  if the player doesn have card to match the one on the discard pile  they must take card from the draw pile  if this can be played  the player is free to put it down in the same turn  otherwise  play moves on to the next person  players may choose not to play playable card from their hand  if so  they must draw card from the draw pile  if playable  that card can be put down in the same turn  but the player may not use card from the hand after the draw  players race to get rid of their cards and the real fun starts when special action cards are used to foil opponents and gain an advantage  with the tension mounting  uno becomes the fun family card game that easy to pick up but impossible to put down  box contains x uno x instruction guide

description: the tk  also known as the tk  tankette was polish design produced from that was based upon an improved chassis of the british carden loyd tankette  the tks was an improved model with new hull and more powerful engine  the armour of the tk was up to   mm thick  mm on the tks in  re arming of the tankettes with   mm machine guns began  but only about were completed before the outbreak of world war ii  the tk tks tankettes formed the bulk of the polish armoured forces before the outbreak of war  they suffered heavy losses during the invasion of poland  often being the only armoured fighting vehicles available  due to their light armament of single machine gun  they stood no chance in combat against german tanks  except the panzer  but their small size suited them for reconnaissance and infantry support  only the handful of tankettes armed with mm guns had fighting chance against the enemy tanks; in one instance on september a mm gunned tks with nkm wz fk commanded by podchorazy or officer candidate in the rank of sfc roman orlik destroyed three german panzerkampfwagen t  tanks  after conquest of poland  the tankettes were taken over and used by the germans  in this role they saw various uses  mostly for training  security duties or artillery tractors  many captured tankettes were used by the luftwaffe for airfield security duties and as snowplows

description: forces of valor   collectionthe king tiger also known as the tiger ii was german heavy tank of wwii  the official german designation was panzerkampfwagen tiger ausf   often shortened to tiger  the ordnance inventory designation was sd  kfz  it is also known under the informal name königstiger translated as king tiger the design followed the same concept as the tiger  but was intended to be even more formidable  the tiger ii combined the thick armor of the tiger with the sloped armor used on the panther medium tank  the tank weighed almost seventy metric tons  was protected by to mm  to   in  of armor to the front and was armed with the long barreled   cm kampfwagenkanone l gun  the chassis was also the basis for the jagdtiger turret less tank destroyer the tiger ii was issued to heavy tank battalions of the army  schwere heeres panzer abteilung abbreviated h pz abt  and the waffen ss  ss pz abt it was first used in combat with h pz abt  during the normandy campaign on july  ;on the eastern front the first unit to be outfitted with tiger iis was h pz abt  which by september listed tiger iis operational the first combat use of the tiger ii was by the company of the heavy tank battalion  h pz abt   during the battle of normandy  opposing operation atlantic between troarn and demouville on july  losses were two from combat  plus the company commander tank which became irrecoverably trapped after falling into bomb crater made during operation goodwood

product description brainbox is fast and fun memory game that does not require any pens  pencils  paper  playing board or even table  each round takes seconds so all players are involved  game lasts as long as you want it to  minutes is the norm  but playing for minutes is great fun also  brainbox is educational and is perfect for families and groups of friends to play  wherever they are  on level playing field  packed in sturdy cool magnetic cube box  brainbox is ready to play without any set up time needed  the rules are pretty straight forward  you can play solo or with as many people as you want  player simply picks card and studies it for seconds before being asked question from the back  chosen by the roll of die  correct answer means the card is kept  if not it is returned to the box  the player with most cards after or minutes wins  the winner may not be who you expect as this fabulous game is about observation and memory  not learned facts  brainbox art includes cards featuring world renowned works of art presented with fun facts and important information about masterpieces and their artists  from van gogh to constable to monet and seurat  manufacturer description the object of the game is to win as many cards as possible in ten minutes  the first player takes card from the brainbox and turns the timer over  the player then has ten seconds to study the picture on the card  when the timer runs out the card is passed to player two and player one rolls the die to see which question is to be asked  the questions are on the reverse of the picture card  player two checks the answer by looking at the picture and if it is correct the card is given back to player one to keep  if the answer is wrong the card is placed back into the brainbox and the next player chooses card  please remember  the answer to the question is on the picture side of the card  so look carefully  the player with the most cards after ten minutes wins  if there is tie  it sudden death with both players choosing card and having to answer all eight questions on the card  the player who answers the most correctly wins  for or more players  ages   contains illustrated cards  rules card  timer and eight sided die  have fun  see all product description

description: corgi scania  face lift  super curtainside trailer  eddie stobart  carlisle   scale diecast manufacturers description  in the eddie stobart built its high profile brand based on the courtesy of its drivers  the quality of its fleet and exceptional service  these benchmark standards remain intact  but stobart also understands the customer service  employment practices and environmental challenges that face modern businesses today  over the last few years the group has evolved beyond its position as an independent road transport and logistics business to leading uk provider of multinational transport and logistics solutions  under new regulations  eddie stobart has introduced new high volume envirotrailer to its ever expanding fleet to help boost the economy  cut congestion and slash carbon emissions from the haulage industry  the eco trailer is being operated under vehicle special order as part of the department for transport   year trial of semi trailers that are one and two metres longer than the then maximum length of   metres  the extended trailers allow operators to carry higher volumes of goods but still meet the current regulations with regard to maximum permitted weights and turning circles  the first uk delivery utilised   metre trailer with two steering rear axles providing impressive manoeuvrability and less wear and tear to the uk road network  the trailer was packed with retail cages and demonstrated  increase in payload allowing for the number of trucks on uk roads to be decreased  this model features the newly tooled super curtainside trailer  please note that this item is not intended to be toy  this item is for collectors  minimum age recommended

description: following the recent introduction of   scale version of the messerschmitt bubble car here at oxford  we now follow through with an equally detailed  newly tooled version in   scale  the messerschmitt  kabinenroller or cabin scooter  was three wheeled bubble car  designed by german aircraft engineer fritz fend and produced in the messerschmitt aircraft factory in regensburg  germany  introduced in  between then and when production ceased  approximately   rolled out of the factory  the oxford replica features hard top rather than the soft top version  the car was designed so that the driver and passenger  riding tandem  got in through canopy door which was hinged on the right side of the vehicle  the door included the windshield and window frames which then closed as monocoque construction over the top of the occupants and was secured on the left hand side  the steering wheel bar was like that in an aircraft and was much more responsive than comparable cars of its time  the engine comprised   cc single cylinder stroke model which was set in front of the rear wheel and behind the passenger seat  there is still lot of interest in this unusual automobile nicknamed  schmitt  today  with enthusiasts all over the world willing to pay over   euros for one  against its original  euros our model is moderately priced in comparison and comes in bright red with clear roof  bubble black chassis and interior floor; bright red dashboard and seating  because the roof opens  the interior is particularly well detailed featuring chrome dashboard panels and steering wheel  there is lot of chrome silver trim on the exterior too  including the hubcaps  the model has uk registration plate cd  emphasising the fact that the tandem format of the driver and passenger seats made the left hand  right hand drive mechanical adjustments unnecessary

description: product description one of the largest users of queen mary’s as staff buses was the british shoe corporation in leicester  in the then foreman  an ex southdown employee  recommended that the company purchase excellently maintained buses which had served his previous employer  leyland titan   kuf became the company’s first staff bus  from a start was made to replace the original fleet with queen marys  the first to arrive were   and  by the mid an all mary fleet was operated and towards the end of the decade newer fleet of queen mary’s replaced the original buses every model in the original omnibus company is recreated in   scale and includes numbered  limited edition certificate  the range includes both modern and classic buses and coaches from some of the best known british manufactures and operators  box contains x diecast x numbered certificate

description: in the early thirties  there were two big names in motorcycle racing which competed with one another on the american tracks; they were harley davidson and indian  at this time  the sportiest bike in the indian range  with top speed of around and good handling  was the scout  in  the company introduced the sport scout  which was pretty much just an improved version of the standard scout model  with heavier and stronger frame for racing  in  ed kretz  who dominated racing stateside for almost decade  won the inaugural daytona on sport scout  in  indian came out with its plunger rear frame and the famous skirted fender  at the same time  the sport scout got lot more finning  to cope with the extra heat that was generated by hauling around the extra weight  it is   model that minichamps has elected to make and we cant disagree with their decision  its great looking bike and truly significant indian it has to be said that were quite impressed with minichamps  indian sport scout  it may not be the heaviest diecast bike weve handled  with more plastic parts than metal ones  but the detail is all there  we like the front suspension with its girder forks and large single spring  the plunger frame  the suspended saddle  the intricately spoked wheels and the skirted front fender  the instruments  the gear change mechanism and the assortment of rods and cables are also rather splendid  this is number in minichamps classic bike collection

boggle is three minute word game for any number of players  you can even play alone  and is suitable for anyone over the age of eight  the game includes the special boggle tray  which is the bottom part of the clear cube container  containing letter dice and sand timer which lasts for three minutes  you must supply your own pens and paper  the dice are placed in the boggle container and given good shake  players must then place the container upright to allow the dice to settle with one letter on each side facing up  the sand timer is set  and you have to make out as many words as possible from the letters facing upwards before the sand timer runs out  the letters used must be from adjoining dice  and you can only use each letter once in any word  words can be singular or plural in form and can be in any tense  so long as they appear in any standard english dictionary  in fact  it is good idea to have one of the main dictionaries of record to hand  for when the inevitable disputes arise there are some other minor rules  all of which are explained in the directions for play  for example  you aren allowed to have foreign words or abbreviations  but the game itself is quite uncomplicated  all you need to bring is good vocabulary  as soon as the timer runs out  every player stops writing immediately  each player then takes it in turns to read out the list of words they have compiled  any word that has been recorded by another player is discounted and does not score  other words score from one point for three or four letter word  up to maximum of points for any word of eight letters or more to win the game  you must be the first player to reach pre agreed score  or the player who has the highest score after pre agreed number of rounds  this is thinking game for adults and an ideal way to extend the vocabulary of the younger players  ben king

people in revolt against television  since its official introduction in  this phenomenally successful board game has been testing game players  wits to the limit  for only in trivial pursuit game will you be asked questions as zany as  was humpty dumpty pushed?" and as difficult as "what modern day animal is related to the prehistoric merychippus?" the historythe game was invented by two canadian journalists in montreal  december   scott abbott former sports editor with the canadian press and chris haney  photo editor for the montreal gazette  after realizing that more help and more money were needed to begin developing their idea  chris older brother john  an ex hockey player  and john friend ed werner  an ex hockey player turned lawyer  were recruited  and the team of abbott  haney  haney and werner got to work having no experience with the games business  it took these four men years of hard work before the trivial pursuit game became seemingly "overnight success" with the public  having depleted almost all of their own money they convinced friends and relatives to buy shares of their company to raise additional capital  the first prototype production test market run of games were sold in canada the trivial pursuit game was first shown in the s  at the american international toy fair in new york city in february  they expected to sell thousands of copies  to their great disappointment  only few hundred were ordered  but they would not give up even after realizing that they were so in debt that if they sold all of the   games ordered from their second production run they would barely break even but there was magic to the game  which had game stores doubling their orders and the media soliciting interviews and the rest  as they say  is history spring marked the anniversary of the universal board game that has sold more than million copies since it was launched and through it all  the highs and lows  abbott  haney  haney and werner have remained the same four
